// claude-sessions: minimal left custom sidebar prototype (task 3.1,
// openspec/changes/add-cmux-sidebar-widgets).
//
// This first pass uses ONLY cmux's natively-free `workspaces` fields — no
// smuggled `description` encoding yet (see docs/cmux-sidebar-encoding.md for
// that scheme, added on top in tasks 3.2/3.3):
//   - directory basename (visually truncated, see FINDING below), then
//     title (Claude Code session name), omitted when empty
//   - branch, with a dirty-indicator dot when dirty is true
//
// FINDING (cmux 0.64.19, live-verified 2026-07-18, task 3.1, beads if-boqe):
// character-position string slicing is NOT supported by cmux's sidebar
// interpreter. Exhaustively tested live via five disposable diagnostic
// sidebars deployed to the real Mac (`~/.config/cmux/sidebars/diag-test{,2,
// 3,4,5}.swift`, validated + opened + inspected via `System Events`
// accessibility-tree text dumps of the real rendered pane — no screen-capture
// access over SSH, so this was the available live-introspection method):
//   - `String(name.prefix(5))`, `"\(name.prefix(5))"`, and bare
//     `name.prefix(5)` concatenation all evaluate to an empty string (or drop
//     the whole containing Text row) — `.prefix(n)`/`.dropFirst(n)` are
//     documented as Array methods only, not String methods, and that holds
//     live: they silently no-op on a String.
//   - `Array(name)` DOES bridge to `[Character]` correctly for `.count`
//     (confirmed: `Array("installfest").count` -> 11), but every path taking
//     a single `Character` back to displayable text fails empty:
//     `.map { String($0) }.joined()`, `.map { "\($0)" }.joined()`, direct
//     interpolation of an array-subscript result (`"\(Array(name)[0])"`),
//     and `"installfest".first` all evaluate empty.
//   - `.split(separator: "")` (empty separator) also evaluates empty/drops
//     the row.
//   - The ONLY confirmed-working string-shortening primitive is
//     `.split(separator: <literal non-empty Character>)` producing
//     multi-character Substrings, where `String(substring)` conversion DOES
//     work (verified: `"installfest".split(separator: "l")` ->
//     `["insta", "fest"]`, `.map { String($0) }.joined(separator: "|")` ->
//     `"insta|fest"`). This is not usable for generic N-character truncation
//     since it depends on a separator character existing at the right
//     position.
// Given this hard interpreter limitation, truncation here is done VISUALLY
// via `.lineLimit(1)` + `.truncationMode(.tail)` + a narrow `.frame` (all
// confirmed-supported modifiers per the authoring guide) rather than a
// literal 5-character string cut. The accessible/underlying text value is
// the FULL basename, not a programmatically-shortened string — this is a
// genuine cmux 0.64.19 interpreter constraint, not an implementation
// shortcut. Follow-up: if a literal string-level truncation is required
// (e.g. for a text-based E2E assertion rather than a visual/pixel check),
// either file the gap upstream to cmux or revisit the spec scenario wording
// to describe visual/frame truncation instead of exact character-count
// truncation.
//
// Deployed via chezmoi to ~/.config/cmux/sidebars/claude-sessions.swift
// (task 3.4 wires the chezmoi source-state; this file has no per-machine
// templating needs today, so it carries no chezmoi template directives despite the
// .tmpl extension — see t3-code-patterns' chezmoi naming convention).
//
// STATE INDICATOR (task 3.2, openspec/changes/add-cmux-sidebar-widgets, beads
// if-n2oq): parses the CC1-prefixed encoding (docs/cmux-sidebar-encoding.md)
// out of `description` and renders an SF-Symbol stand-in for the Claude mark,
// solid when idle, pulsating when active, pulsing red when waiting on a
// permission prompt.
//
// FINDING (cmux 0.64.19, live-verified 2026-07-18, beads if-n2oq): the
// encoding doc's own reader-contract pseudocode --
// `description.split(separator: "|", omittingEmptySubsequences: false)` then
// expecting exactly 8 segments -- does NOT work. The interpreter silently
// ignores the `omittingEmptySubsequences` argument and always omits empty
// subsequences (the actual Swift default, true), so splitting a real CC1
// string like "CC1|idle||1737158765||||" (8 fields, 3 empty) yields
// segs.count == 3, not 8 -- confirmed live via a disposable diagnostic
// sidebar deployed to the real Mac, seeded via `cmux workspace-action
// --action set-description` against a disposable test workspace, and
// inspected via a System Events accessibility-tree text dump of the
// diagnostic's own rendered Text output (no Screen Recording TCC grant over
// SSH, same substitute method task 3.1 used). This breaks positional 8-field
// indexing for any real-world CC1 string, since most fields are legitimately
// empty. WORKAROUND: because the encoding's fields are fixed-order, `state`
// and `wait_reason` can be identified by exact-prefix match instead --
// `hasPrefix("CC1|idle|")` etc. -- which sidesteps `.split` entirely (the
// trailing `|` after each vocabulary token disambiguates it from any other
// field value, since none of the 3 state tokens is a prefix of another).
// Live-verified against the real disposable test workspace
// (cmux-evolve-test-if-n2oq-v2): seeding `CC1|idle||...`, `CC1|active||...`,
// and `CC1|waiting|permission|...` in turn onto the workspace's description
// each produced the correct `cc1Mode` classification (confirmed via a
// diagnostic sidebar rendering the classified string as text), and a real
// SwiftUI Image element appeared in the AX-tree dump in the exact position
// this indicator renders for all three -- while workspaces with no CC1 state
// yet (`if`, empty `state` field) or no description at all (`brown`/`tc`)
// correctly rendered zero image elements, matching the fail-closed
// "unparseable renders no indicator" requirement without any extra code path
// (the same hasPrefix fallthrough already covers "no known state").
//
// `clock.second` (live data, re-rendered ~1/sec) drives the active/waiting
// pulse via `clock.second % 2` parity, mirroring cc-tmux's own tick-based
// pulse (`apps/cc-tmux/src/cc_tmux/render.py`) -- confirmed live to be a real,
// changing wall-clock value across captures (observed seconds 17, 49, 46;
// parities 1, 1, 0), so the alternation is driven by real time, not a static
// value.
//
// OPENSPEC/BEADS ROW + USAGE FOOTER (task 3.3,
// openspec/changes/add-cmux-sidebar-widgets, beads if-6to1): reads the
// smuggled `openspec` (segment 4), `beads` (segment 5), `usage_5h` (segment
// 6), `usage_7d` (segment 7) fields populated by scripts/cmux-status-writer.py
// (task 2.4).
//
// FINDING (cmux 0.64.19, beads if-n2oq/if-6to1): positional field indexing was
// unrecoverable through cmux's split (empty-subsequence collapse, see the
// STATE INDICATOR finding above and docs/cmux-sidebar-encoding.md § Empty-field
// sentinel). RESOLVED writer-side, not reader-side: the shared encoder now
// substitutes a `-` sentinel for every empty field
// (scripts/lib/cmux_status_encoding.py), so an encoded string has ZERO empty
// segments and a plain `.split(separator: "|")` reliably returns all 8. The
// `cc1Field` helper below indexes positionally on that guarantee and maps the
// `-` sentinel back to "" (fail-closed to "" on any wrong-shape string, e.g. a
// pre-sentinel old-format description whose split still collapses -- so the
// smuggled-field rows simply don't render until the next writer pass upgrades
// the string, never a crash). The task 3.2 state indicator above is
// deliberately left on its `hasPrefix` matching, which is strictly more robust
// (works even on a collapsing old-format string) and needs no change for the
// sentinel form (`CC1|idle|-|...` still has prefix `CC1|idle|`).
//
// Usage footer thresholds are ported from apps/cc-tmux/src/cc_tmux/usage.py's
// `color_for` at integer-percent granularity (the encoding stores usage as an
// integer percent, not the 0..1 float `color_for` takes): `> 80` -> RED,
// `>= 50` -> YELLOW, else CYAN -- i.e. p>80 <=> util>0.80 and p>=50 <=>
// util>=0.50 for integer p, a faithful 1:1 port of color_for's boundaries. The
// footer is rendered once per panel (not per row): per
// docs/cmux-sidebar-encoding.md § Usage Carrier the usage figures live on
// exactly one carrier workspace's description, so a post-list `ForEach` that
// renders a meter only for the row whose `usage_5h` is non-empty yields exactly
// one footer (and none when no carrier is present -- the spec's "missing usage
// data renders no footer" scenario) without needing collection-accumulation
// primitives the interpreter lacks.

// Positional CC1 field extractor (docs/cmux-sidebar-encoding.md § Swift reader
// contract). Depends on the writer-side `-` sentinel so `.split` returns all 8
// segments; returns "" for a wrong-shape string, the magic slot, or the "-"
// sentinel. Index map: 0=CC1 1=state 2=wait_reason 3=epoch 4=openspec 5=beads
// 6=usage_5h 7=usage_7d.
func cc1Field(_ d: String, _ index: Int) -> String {
    let segs = d.split(separator: "|")
    if segs.count != 8 {
        return ""
    }
    let v = String(segs[index])
    if v == "-" {
        return ""
    }
    return v
}

func basename(_ path: String) -> String {
    let parts = path.split(separator: "/")
    if parts.count > 0 {
        return String(parts[parts.count - 1])
    }
    return path
}

// Classify a workspace's `description` per the CC1 encoding, using
// exact-prefix match instead of positional `.split` (see FINDING above).
// Returns "none" for empty/absent/unparseable/unhandled-combination
// descriptions -- the caller renders no indicator for that case.
func cc1Mode(_ d: String) -> String {
    if d.hasPrefix("CC1|idle|") {
        return "idle"
    } else if d.hasPrefix("CC1|active|") {
        return "active"
    } else if d.hasPrefix("CC1|waiting|permission|") {
        return "waiting"
    } else {
        return "none"
    }
}

VStack(alignment: .leading, spacing: 0) {
    Text("Claude Sessions").font(.headline)
    Divider()
    ForEach(workspaces) { w in
        VStack(alignment: .leading, spacing: 2) {
            HStack(spacing: 4) {
                if let d = w.description {
                    let mode = cc1Mode(d)
                    let pulseOpacity = clock.second % 2 == 0 ? 1.0 : 0.35
                    if mode == "idle" {
                        Image(systemName: "sparkle")
                            .foregroundColor(.secondary)
                            .accessibilityLabel("Claude state: idle")
                    } else if mode == "active" {
                        Image(systemName: "sparkle")
                            .foregroundColor(.orange)
                            .opacity(pulseOpacity)
                            .accessibilityLabel("Claude state: active")
                    } else if mode == "waiting" {
                        Image(systemName: "sparkle")
                            .foregroundColor(.red)
                            .opacity(pulseOpacity)
                            .accessibilityLabel("Claude state: waiting for permission")
                    }
                }
                Text(basename(w.directory))
                    .font(.system(.body, design: .monospaced))
                    .foregroundColor(.primary)
                    .lineLimit(1)
                    .truncationMode(.tail)
                    .frame(maxWidth: 44, alignment: .leading)
                if !w.title.isEmpty {
                    Text(w.title)
                        .font(.system(.body))
                        .foregroundColor(.secondary)
                }
                Spacer()
            }
            HStack(spacing: 4) {
                if let branch = w.branch {
                    Text(branch)
                        .font(.system(.caption, design: .monospaced))
                        .foregroundColor(.secondary)
                    if let dirty = w.dirty {
                        if dirty {
                            Text("●")
                                .font(.system(.caption))
                                .foregroundColor(.orange)
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
            // openspec / beads smuggled-field row (task 3.3). Each segment is
            // rendered only when the writer populated it; both empty -> the
            // HStack renders nothing (zero-height), no extra guard needed.
            if let d = w.description {
                let openspecSummary = cc1Field(d, 4)
                let beadsSummary = cc1Field(d, 5)
                HStack(spacing: 8) {
                    if !openspecSummary.isEmpty {
                        Text("◇ \(openspecSummary)")
                            .font(.system(.caption, design: .monospaced))
                            .foregroundColor(.secondary)
                            .lineLimit(1)
                            .truncationMode(.tail)
                    }
                    if !beadsSummary.isEmpty {
                        Text("● \(beadsSummary)")
                            .font(.system(.caption, design: .monospaced))
                            .foregroundColor(.secondary)
                            .lineLimit(1)
                            .truncationMode(.tail)
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        .padding(.vertical, 4)
        .onTapGesture { cmux("workspace.select", workspace_id: w.id) }
        Divider()
    }
    // Compact usage-meter footer (task 3.3), rendered once per panel from the
    // single usage-carrier workspace (docs/cmux-sidebar-encoding.md § Usage
    // Carrier). Only the carrier's `usage_5h` is non-empty, so this renders
    // exactly one row -- and none when no carrier is present (the spec's
    // "missing usage data renders no footer" scenario). Threshold colors are
    // ported from usage.py `color_for` at integer-percent granularity: >80 RED,
    // >=50 YELLOW, else CYAN.
    ForEach(workspaces) { w in
        if let d = w.description {
            let usage5h = cc1Field(d, 6)
            let usage7d = cc1Field(d, 7)
            if !usage5h.isEmpty {
                HStack(spacing: 8) {
                    Text("Usage")
                        .font(.system(.caption, design: .monospaced))
                        .foregroundColor(.secondary)
                    if let u5 = Int(usage5h) {
                        Text("5H \(usage5h)%")
                            .font(.system(.caption, design: .monospaced))
                            .foregroundColor(u5 > 80 ? .red : (u5 >= 50 ? .yellow : .cyan))
                    }
                    if let u7 = Int(usage7d) {
                        Text("7D \(usage7d)%")
                            .font(.system(.caption, design: .monospaced))
                            .foregroundColor(u7 > 80 ? .red : (u7 >= 50 ? .yellow : .cyan))
                    }
                    Spacer()
                }
                .padding(.vertical, 4)
            }
        }
    }
}
.padding(8)
